main event: On April 25, 1956, in Seattle, Washington, a round, white object, half the size of the spoke of a bicycle wheel, was observed ascending in the WSW direction for 7-10 seconds.
interesting points: The object was described as white, round, and half the size of a bicycle wheel spoke, ascending in the WSW direction.
The observation lasted for 7-10 seconds, and the object appeared to be rising and traveling towards the WSW.
The conclusion drawn was that it was probably astronomical, possibly indicating a meteor.
The report mentions a witness who was a 23-year-old draftsman at Boeing Aircraft Corp, adding credibility to the observation.
The document does not contain any photographs of the observed object.
